Tokyo stocks end volatile trade slightly lower . Tokyo stocks closed slightly lower on Tuesday after a day of volatile trade . The Nikkei average ' s decline , which continued from Monday , induced some buying back in late trade , but the bottom side is likely to be still vulnerable , brokers said . The key Nikkei 225 average was down 44 . 13 points , or 0 . 21 percent , at 20 , 630 . 56 . Its December futures were 20 points lower at 20 , 660 . The Nikkei index briefly slipped to 20 , 478 . 74 in mid - afternoon , partly due to speculative futures sales and weaker blue - chip issues , they said . 
